16. 
17. **What are migrations?**  
18. Think of migrations as version control for your database. Instead of manually creating tables in MySQL or SQLite, you write PHP code that Laravel executes to build your database schema. This has huge benefits:
19. 
20. - **Version controlled**: Your database structure is tracked in git
21. - **Reversible**: You can undo changes with `php artisan migrate:rollback`
22. - **Shareable**: Your teammates get the same database structure automatically
23. - **Deployable**: Production servers can be set up with a single command
24. 
25. **The Up/Down Pattern**  
26. Every migration has two methods:
27. 
28. ```php
29. public function up(): void
30. {
31.     // What to do when migrating forward
32.     Schema::create('photos', function (Blueprint $table) {
33.         $table->id();
34.         $table->string('title');
35.         $table->timestamps();
36.     });
37. }
38. 
39. public function down(): void
40. {
41.     // How to undo this migration
42.     Schema::dropIfExists('photos');
43. }
44. ```
45. 
46. **Running Migrations**
47. 
48. ```bash
49. # Run all pending migrations
50. php artisan migrate
